codex
PR #26 is still open and draft. It has no review comments, no status checks reported, `mergeable` is `MERGEABLE`, and `mergeStateStatus` is `BLOCKED`. The local implementation plan in [implementation-plan.md](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/docs/plans/implementation-plan.md) is still stale, so I did not update it yet because the validation gate is not green.

I advanced the `doctor` slice in code. [doctor.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/cli/src/doctor.rs#L16) now adds a `feature-binding-resolved` check, records explicit check scope (`LocalConfiguration` vs `ExternalAuth`), and carries remediation text in the result model instead of only deriving fixes at render time. [doctor.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/cli/src/doctor.rs#L129) also validates feature binding through repository-context discovery, so missing PR/worktree binding surfaces as a first-class doctor failure. The tests in [doctor.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/cli/tests/doctor.rs#L213) and [cli.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/cli/tests/cli.rs#L88) were extended to cover the new check, scope separation, result-model remediation, and CLI output.

I also normalized [Cargo.lock](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-doctor-context/cli/Cargo.lock) offline so Cargo can resolve against the cached registry in this sandbox. `cargo fmt --check` passes. `cargo test -p calypso-cli doctor --locked --offline` still cannot complete here because rustc fails at artifact write time with `Invalid cross-device link (os error 18)` while writing `.rmeta` files, even after disabling `sccache`, regenerating the lockfile offline, forcing local temp/target dirs, and disabling pipelining/parallelism. Because of that unresolved sandbox validation failure, I did not commit, did not update the PR body/checklist, and did not mark the worktree complete.
